TITLE: Configuring Consul Service Mesh with Connect in Nomad
DESCRIPTION: An example of a service block specified at the group level that includes a connect block for Consul Service Mesh integration. This configuration creates and registers a service named "count-api" with Consul Service Mesh, enabling service mesh features like sidecar proxies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/index.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
service {
       name = "count-api"
       port = "9001"

       connect {
         sidecar_service {}
       }
     }
```

