TITLE: Implementing Dynamic Blocks in Nomad HCL Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive example of using dynamic blocks to generate repeatable nested blocks based on local variables. This demonstrates iterating over a collection to create multiple port configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/hcl2/expressions.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
locals {
  ports = [
    {
      port_label = "api"
      port       = 80
    },
    {
      port_label = "ui"
      port       = 8080
    }
  ]
}

job "example" {
  datacenters = ["dc1"]

  group "cache" {
    network {

      mode = "host"

      dynamic "port" {
        for_each = local.ports
        labels   = [port.value.port_label]

        content {
          to = port.value.port
        }
      }
    }
    ...
```

