TITLE: Configuring Comprehensive TLS Settings in Nomad
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a more comprehensive TLS configuration for a Nomad agent. It enables TLS for HTTP and RPC, specifies paths for CA certificate, agent certificate, and private key files. This setup enables mutual TLS (mTLS) communication between all servers and clients.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/configuration/tls.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
tls {
  http = true
  rpc  = true

  ca_file   = "/etc/certs/ca.crt"
  cert_file = "/etc/certs/nomad.crt"
  key_file  = "/etc/certs/nomad.key"
}
```

