TITLE: Declaring Input Variables with Type Constraints in Nomad HCL
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to declare input variables with various type constraints including string, list of strings, and a complex object type for Docker ports configuration. Each variable can have type definitions and default values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/hcl2/variables.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
variable "image_id" {
  type = string
}

variable "availability_zone_names" {
  type    = list(string)
  default = ["us-west-1a"]
}

variable "docker_ports" {
  type = list(object({
    internal = number
    external = number
    protocol = string
  }))
  default = [
    {
      internal = 8300
      external = 8300
      protocol = "tcp"
    }
  ]
}
```

