TITLE: Setting Metadata and Environment Variables for a Task in HCL
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use custom metadata and environment variables to pass information to a task. It uses the 'exec' driver to run a command.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/task.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
task "server" {
  driver = "exec"
  config {
    command = "/bin/env"
  }

  meta {
    my-key = "my-value"
  }

  env {
    MY_KEY = "${meta.my-key}"
  }

  resources {
    cpu = 20
  }
}
```

