TITLE: Basic HCL Syntax for Nomad Job Specification
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the basic syntax elements of HCL used in Nomad job specifications. It shows the structure of blocks, arguments, and expressions, which are the fundamental components of HCL configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/hcl2/index.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
task "example" {
  driver = "docker"
}

<BLOCK TYPE> "<BLOCK LABEL>" {
  # Block body
  <IDENTIFIER> = <EXPRESSION> # Argument
}
```

