TITLE: Configuring a Docker Container Task in HCL
DESCRIPTION: This example defines a task that starts a Docker container as a service. It specifies the Docker driver, image, and arguments, as well as resource requirements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/task.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
task "server" {
  driver = "docker"
  config {
    image = "hashicorp/http-echo"
    args  = ["-text", "hello world"]
  }

  resources {
    cpu = 20
  }
}
```

