TITLE: Rendering Environment Variables with Nomad Templates (HCL)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use Nomad templates to render environment variables for a task, including handling of special characters and secrets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/template.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
template {
  data = <<EOH
# Empty lines are also ignored
LOG_LEVEL="{{key "service/geo-api/log-verbosity"}}"
API_KEY="{{with secret "secret/geo-api-key"}}{{.Data.value}}{{end}}"
EOH

  destination = "secrets/file.env"
  env         = true
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Accessing Consul KV and Service Data in Nomad Templates (HCL)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to retrieve single key values and lists of keys from Consul's KV store, and how to query the Consul service catalog for service information within Nomad template blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/template.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
  template {
    data = <<EOF
# Read single key from Consul KV.
APP_NAME = "{{key "app/name"}}"

# Read all keys in the path `app/environment` from Consul KV.
{{range ls "app/environment"}}
{{.Key}}={{.Value}}
{{end}}
    EOF

    destination = "local/env"
    env         = true
  }
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring change_script in Nomad Job Specification (HCL)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure a change_script block within a Nomad job specification. It shows the structure and parameters for executing a script when a template changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/change_script.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
job "docs" {
  group "example" {
    task "server" {
      template {
        source      = "local/redis.conf.tpl"
        destination = "local/redis.conf"
        change_mode = "script"
        change_script {
          command       = "/bin/foo"
          args          = ["-verbose", "-debug"]
          timeout       = "5s"
          fail_on_error = false
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

