TITLE: Configuring Upstreams in a Consul Connect Sidecar Proxy
DESCRIPTION: An example of configuring upstreams in a sidecar service proxy block. This configuration specifies that the proxy should connect to the 'count-api' service and make it available locally on port 8080.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/proxy.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
sidecar_service {
  proxy {
    upstreams {
      destination_name = "count-api"
      local_bind_port  = 8080
    }
  }
}
```

