TITLE: Configuring Redis Service with Docker Driver and Weave Network
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a complete job configuration for a Redis service using the Docker driver with Weave network. It includes network, task, and service configurations with health checks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/service.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
job "example" {
  datacenters = ["dc1"]

  group "cache" {
    network {
      port "db" {
        to = 6379
      }
    }

    task "redis" {
      driver = "docker"

      config {
        image = "redis:7"
        network_mode = "weave"
        ports = ["db"]
      }

      resources {
        cpu    = 500 # 500 MHz
        memory = 256 # 256MB
      }

      service {
        name = "weave-redis"
        port = "db"
        check {
          name     = "host-redis-check"
          type     = "tcp"
          interval = "10s"
          timeout  = "2s"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

