TITLE: Configuring Volume Mount for a Task in Nomad HCL Job Specification
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to define a volume at the group level and mount it within a task. It shows a read-only host volume named 'certs' being mounted to '/etc/ssl/certs' with private propagation mode.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/volume_mount.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
job "docs" {
  group "example" {
    volume "certs" {
      type = "host"
      read_only = true
      source = "ca-certificates"
    }

    task "example" {
      volume_mount {
        volume      = "certs"
        destination = "/etc/ssl/certs"
        propagation_mode = "private"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

