TITLE: Configuring Redis Service with Driver Address Mode
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a job configuration for a Redis service using the Docker driver with Weave network, demonstrating the use of driver address mode for both service and check blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/service.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
job "example" {
  datacenters = ["dc1"]
  group "cache" {

    task "redis" {
      driver = "docker"

      config {
        image = "redis:7"
        network_mode = "weave"
        # No port map required.
      }

      resources {
        cpu    = 500 # 500 MHz
        memory = 256 # 256MB
      }

      service {
        name = "weave-redis"
        port = 6379
        address_mode = "driver"
        check {
          name     = "host-redis-check"
          type     = "tcp"
          interval = "10s"
          timeout  = "2s"
          port     = 6379

          address_mode = "driver"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

