TITLE: Creating peers.json for Single Nomad Server Upgrade
DESCRIPTION: This Bash script creates a peers.json file required for upgrading a single Nomad server to Raft protocol version 3. It extracts the Nomad data directory, leader address, and node ID from the running server to construct a valid peers.json file in the raft directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/upgrade/index.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
#!/usr/bin/env bash

NOMAD_DATA_DIR=$(nomad agent-info -json | jq -r '.config.DataDir')
NOMAD_ADDR=$(nomad agent-info -json | jq -r '.stats.nomad.leader_addr')
NODE_ID=$(cat "$NOMAD_DATA_DIR/server/node-id")

cat <<EOF > "$NOMAD_DATA_DIR/server/raft/peers.json"
[
  {
    "id": "$NODE_ID",
    "address": "$NOMAD_ADDR",
    "non_voter": false
  }
]
EOF
```

