TITLE: Practical Example of Range Function in HCL
DESCRIPTION: A practical example demonstrating how to use the range function with other collections to produce a certain number of instances. It uses a map of name counts to generate expanded names with numbered suffixes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/job-specification/hcl2/functions/collection/range.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
variable "name_counts" {
  type    = map(number)
  default = {
    "foo" = 2
    "bar" = 4
  }
}

locals {
  expanded_names = {
    for name, count in var.name_counts : name => [
      for i in range(count) : format("%s%02d", name, i)
    ]
  }
}

output "expanded_names" {
  value = local.expanded_names
}

# Produces the following expanded_names value when run with the default
# "name_counts":
#
# {
#   "bar" = [
#     "bar00",
#     "bar01",
#     "bar02",
#     "bar03",
#   ]
#   "foo" = [
#     "foo00",
#     "foo01",
#   ]
# }
```

