TITLE: Using Java Version Constraints in Nomad Job
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use Java client attributes in a job constraint to ensure the job runs only on nodes with a specific Java version.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/drivers/java.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
job "docs" {
  # Only run this job where the JVM is higher than version 1.6.0.
  constraint {
    attribute = "${attr.driver.java.version}"
    operator  = ">"
    value     = "1.6.0"
  }
}
```

