TITLE: Proper Object Mutation Patterns in Nomad
DESCRIPTION: Shows the correct approach for modifying objects retrieved from the state store. Objects must be copied before mutation to prevent inconsistent state across servers, transaction failures, and potential panics.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/contributing/architecture-state-store.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
# Incorrect: job is mutated without copying.
job, err := state.JobByID(ws, namespace, id)
job.Status = structs.JobStatusRunning

# Correct: only the job copy is mutated.
job, err := state.JobByID(ws, namespace, id)
updateJob := job.Copy()
updateJob.Status = structs.JobStatusRunning
```

