TITLE: Configuring Nomad with Consul TLS for Service Mesh
DESCRIPTION: HCL configuration for Nomad to work with Consul Connect when TLS is enabled. Required for Consul 1.14+ which made backwards incompatible changes to TLS-enabled GRPC listeners.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/nomad/blob/main/website/content/docs/integrations/consul/service-mesh.mdx#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
consul {
  grpc_ca_file = "/etc/tls/consul-agent-ca.pem"
  grpc_address = "127.0.0.1:8503"
  ca_file      = "/etc/tls/consul-agent-ca.pem"
  cert_file    = "/etc/tls/dc1-client-consul-0.pem"
  key_file     = "/etc/tls/dc1-client-consul-0-key.pem"
  ssl          = true
  address      = "127.0.0.1:8501"
}
```

